<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Location: London</li>
	<li>9 week programme from June - August</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent) in a Science/Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related science or engineering discipline will be relevant</li>
	<li>Fluency in English</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">Enterprise Change, Technology  &amp; Operations (ECT &amp;O) facilitate Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch customer, client and employee requirements through the implementation of technology, systems, call centres and various tools and channels.</p>
<p class="bac">The Summer Internship programme is designed to develop highly motivated technologists and is a pipeline to the Graduate Placement programme. Interns are placed into challenging rolls across ECT &amp;O with the opportunity to work on projects and business support, unique to one of the world&#39;s largest Banks.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As a Summer Analyst, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Participate in design, development and implementation of complex systems/applications often using new technologies in support of business goals</li>
	<li>Analyse, track and troubleshoot performance of an assigned system or network to ensure that all information processing and delivery requirements are met</li>
	<li>Provide project management support relating to process improvements in technology</li>
	<li>Provide analytical support for data collection and measurements</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The programme is designed to help you decide whether our offer matches your aspirations and includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>One week induction and training programme with classroom instruction</li>
	<li>A buddy and mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring global  &amp; divisional presentations by top executives</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>A passion and interest in technology</li>
	<li>A Bachelor&#39;s, Master&#39;s, or Doctorate degree in Computer Science/Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related science or engineering discipline will be relevant</li>
	<li>An ability to work in a fast paced environment whilst multi tasking  &amp; interacting with a wide variety of people</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

